Latin American Coffee Exports Fell 13% in August, Group Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-09-20T16:48:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/latin-american-coffee-exports-fell-13-in-august-group-says-1-.html
Coffee exports from  Colombia ,
 Mexico  and seven other Latin American countries fell 13 percent
in August from a year earlier.  Total shipments dropped to 1.545 million bags from 1.766
million bags, Guatemala’s National Coffee Association, or
 Anacafe , said in a report e-mailed today.  Exports from Colombia, the world’s second-largest producer
of arabica beans, slid 38 percent to 374,000 bags. Mexican
deliveries gained 20 percent to 215,247 bags, the data showed.  The following figures are from Anacafe, citing data from
the countries for production of mild washed arabica beans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
 ialmeida3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 